text: Muribaculum intestinale is a strictly anaerobic bacterium from the genus of Muribaculum which has been isolated from the caecal content of a mouse in Zurich in Switzerland. == References == ==External links== *Type strain of Muribaculum intestinale at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase Category:Bacteroidetes Category:Bacteria described in 2016
title: Muribaculum intestinale
